cap), widow and used to work in a show factory, Heil and Co., Milwaukee, Wisconsin. Agnes Cliemka, age 23, married and husband may be going into the service any day, brother in the army. [She] used to be a clerk in a dep[artmen]t store. Unmasking and checking parts of the gasoline trailers that will be turned over to the Air Force", "type": ["still image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017878342/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_hodag_ver01/data/sn86086499/0041421440A/1911022401/0058.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_hodag_ver01:data:sn86086499:0041421440A:1911022401:0057/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_hodag_ver01/data/sn86086499/0041421440A/1911022401/0058.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86086499/1911-02-24/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_hodag_ver01/data/sn86086499/0041421440A/1911022401/0058.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_hodag_ver01:data:sn86086499:0041421440A:1911022401:0057/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_hodag_ver01/data/sn86086499/0041421440A/1911022401/0058.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86086499/1911-02-24/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_hodag_ver01/data/sn86086499/0041421440A/1911022401/0058.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86086499/1911-02-24/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["whi_hodag_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/wisconsin/", "2/united states/wisconsin/milwaukee/", "3/united states/wisconsin/milwaukee/wauwatosa/"], "contributor": ["wisconsin historical society"], "date": "1911-02-24", "dates": ["1911-02-24"], "description": ["WAUWATOSA NEWS WAUWATOSA WIS J R BENOY Publisher Beware the grip Do not let It get a hold on you Pride has many a fall these slip pery mornings Baseball talk has moved on from postmortems to forecasts An extraordinary duel was fought In France the other day One of the duellists was hurt Chicago is the gem center of the world but thore is such a thing as wearing too many Baseball bids fair to girdle the globe The Japs and the Cubans are taking kindly to it One mans attempt at suicide is at tributed to too much housework Is this a sign of the times We are told that an Illinois woman has put an end to herself by Jumping into a cistern Well well What do you think of a hen that laid 4000 eggs in 22 years and never brooded Can you beat It The house cat carries germs in doors and indulges out of doors In an excess of vocal expression Florida has a bride seventyeight years old And yet there are women of forty who have given up hope A New York publisher tells us that poor music sells best So we should"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-22T16:20:44.669Z", "group": ["ndnp/whi", "wisconsin-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86086499/1911-02-24/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_hodag_ver01:data:sn86086499:0041421440A:1911022401:0058/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=288&w=206", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_hodag_ver01:data:sn86086499:0041421440A:1911022401:0058/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=577&w=413", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_hodag_ver01:data